data.title: Petses. We has them.

images.title: Aki Momo
images.description: The one female cat, and she is The Queen of the catocracy that was established as soon as we brought them home from my hubby's parent's house, due to begging children (and grandparents who had not planned on preggers cat). She was hubby's now passed sister's favorite, so no matter how mad she's made me, when getting into things or making messes, or tearing things up ... I just can't stay mad for long. It's like having a connection to her still here. And boy doesn't this little diva know it.

images.title: Tiger
images.description: He was the runt of the litter, and now he's HUGE. I absolutely love his ear fluffles, and how his fuzzy belly curls, as does Aki's - she's his sister. He has the longest whiskers, and is utterly shy of anyone that isn't family. He'll run and hide as soon as he hears anyone at the door, and won't come out until he feel safe. He'll sit and watch the birds outside, and chirp at them quietly.

images.title: Sammi
images.description: Sammi is our rescue story. He loves /everyone/, and is the chillest cat that ever catted. Ex-boyfriend of daughter's had hidden him, then didn't take care of him, letting him live of pizza scraps and whatever else he could scrounge in the apartment-turned-crack-house. Covered in fleas, and barely able to walk from weakness, daughter stormed in on finding out, took him on threat of offering much-deserved ass-beatings, and got him to the vet. Another week, and he'd have been gone, they said. It's like he knows it. Now he's content, fat, and sassy. We wouldn't have him any other way.
